Ask HN: Who are your favorite devs to follow on GitHub who star a lot?
text:
I believe that following the "best" devs on GitHub is a great way to stay up-to-date with the most interesting new projects in my areas of interest (mostly JS / TS / Rust / WebGL / React).

A lot of devs do great on social but aren't as active on GitHub, and conversely, a lot of devs are really active on GitHub but post less on social media, so their reach is much more limited.

So HN: who are your favorite devs to follow on GitHub who provide the best signal-to-noise ratio for staying up-to-date about the latest & greatest OSS projects??

Ask HN: Using GoDaddy's domain broker service for expired domains?
text:
There's a domain I'm interested in that appears to have already expired; its WHOIS information lists its status as `clientRenewProhibited`. Though the actual expiration is in a couple months, considering it was registered through GoDaddy, I have a feeling they will simply renew the domain themselves and then squat on it. When I go to register it now, GoDaddy claims it's taken, but they can use the "domain broker service" to help negotiate for it. Since the actual owner isn't in control anymore, I find this to be suspect.

Does anyone have experience using the GoDaddy Domain Broker Service successfully? Bonus points if you're using it on a domain that has already or is about to expire.
